    <div class="col-12" "col-m-12">
      <h3>Important Notes:</h3>
      <ol>
	<li>
	  The blue areas mark predicted ranges from the global climate
          models used in the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change,
          Fourth Assessement Report (<a href="https://www.ipcc.ch/report/ar4/syr/">IPCC AR4, 2007</a>).
	</li>
	<li>
	  The estimated global temperature response is a rough scaling
	  based upon average IPCC AR4 (2007) model sensitivity to
	  atmospheric CO<sub>2</sub>.  It is for illustrative purposes
	  only.
	</li>
	<li>
	  Output of atmospheric CO<sub>2</sub> for input to the EdGCM
	  (<a href="http://edgcm.columbia.edu">Educational Global Climate Model</a>)
	  can be obtained by clicking on the EdGCM button.  Place this
	  file in the file EdGCM / Input Forcings on your computer and
	  you will then see the file under Setup Simulations - CO<sub>2</sub> Trend
	  - data file one you start EdGCM.  This functionality has been
	  tested to work on Chrome and Firefox.
	</li>
	<li>
	  Testing link to nowhere: <a href="example.com">example link</a>.
	  Should always be "unvisited" so all link colors are shown on
	  the page.
	</li>
      </ol>
